"```sql\nSELECT DISTINCT Patient.Diagnosis\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.DNA > 8;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects distinct diagnoses from the `Patient` table for patients who have an abnormal level of anti-DNA, defined as a DNA level greater than or equal to 8, as per the evidence provided. The query joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables using the `ID` column, which is a foreign key relationship."